    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen both `vim.o.autocomplete` and CodeLens are enabled for a buffer, there's a weird issue when cursor in insert mode moves back by one character automatically when it's placed at the end of the line, making typing really hard.\n\nThis is 100% reproducible for all lines of a go.mod file, but only for some lines of yaml files.\n\nDisabling just one, CodeLens or autocomplete solves the issue.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f75be954-1ed6-4d64-91e8-8db07be4e7d2\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMinimal init.lua:\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config['gopls'] = {\n  cmd = { 'gopls' },\n  filetypes = { 'gomod' },\n}\nvim.lsp.enable('gopls')\n\nvim.lsp.codelens.enable(true)\nvim.o.autocomplete=true\n```\ngo.mod for tests:\n```go\nmodule github.com/neovim/neovim\n\ngo 1.26\n```\n\n1. Open go.mod\n2. press `A`, see the cursor to go back one char in insert mode\n3. try writing, see the cursor moving back after small delay but only if writing at the end of the line\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor not moving back automatically.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-nightly+ d5516da\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnewest macOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix",
