            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "When normal! zb is executed via ex_normal, it temporarily switches State to NORMAL, which causes check_cursor_col to misdetect the current mode and clamp the cursor position. As a result, a cursor position that should be valid in insert mode (col == len) gets incorrectly clamped.\n\nthese code from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37985\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/1685ced33551ec9c01fc0296f2f6566d14f65b26/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua#L272-L276\n\nthis seems work\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua\nindex 30b4c4a8ca..051d0ea4b3 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua\n@@ -272,7 +272,21 @@ function Provider:on_win(toprow, botrow)\n           -- Fix https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/16166\n           -- Make sure the code lens on the first line is visible when updating.\n           if row == 0 then\n-            vim.cmd('normal! zb')\n+            if vim.startswith(api.nvim_get_mode().mode, 'i') then\n+              vim.schedule(function()\n+                local win = bufnr and vim.fn.bufwinid(bufnr) or -1\n+                if win == -1 then\n+                  return\n+                end\n+                api.nvim_win_call(win, function()\n+                  local view = vim.fn.winsaveview()\n+                  vim.cmd('normal! zb')\n+                  vim.fn.winrestview(view)\n+                end)\n+              end)\n+            else\n+              vim.cmd('normal! zb')\n+            end\n           end\n         end\n         self.row_version[row] = self.version\n```",
